qas.question: Which Cypriot tennis player ranked 8th in the world?
How high did Kyriakos Ioannou jump in Osaka in 2007?
What organization does Costas Philippou participate in?

answers.text: GP3 Series for Marussia Manor Motorsport

context: Tennis player <a0_0>Marcos Baghdatis<a0_0/> was ranked 8th in the world, was a finalist at the Australian Open, and reached the Wimbledon semi-final, all in 2006. High jumper Kyriakos Ioannou achieved a jump of <a1_0>2.35 m<a1_0/> at the 11th IAAF World Championships in Athletics in Osaka, Japan, in 2007, winning the bronze medal. He has been ranked third in the world. In motorsports, Tio Ellinas is a successful race car driver, currently racing in the <a3_0>GP3 Series for Marussia Manor Motorsport<a3_0/>. There is also mixed martial artist Costas Philippou, who competes in the <a2_0>Ultimate Fighting Championship<a2_0/> promotion's middleweight division. Costas holds a 6-3 record in UFC bouts, and recently defeated "The Monsoon" Lorenz Larkin with a Knockout in the 1st round.
